name: (F-31) Cute Sun-filled, Fenway Apartment!
neighborhood_overview: "The sprawling Fenway-Kenmore area is home to baseballâ€™s iconic Fenway Park, drawing huge crowds for Red Sox games. Student hangouts and buzzy restaurants are concentrated around Kenmore Square, and clubs and sports bars line Lansdowne Street. Renowned cultural institutions include the Museum of Fine Arts and quirky Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum. The rambling Back Bay Fens park has a rose garden and walking trails."
description:
Stay healthy with us! With all the craziness going on around us, feel comfortable knowing that our cleaners are wiping down everything! We are wiping down door knobs, keypads, and keeping our environments clean! Avoid the busy hotels and large common areas, Stay safe, clean and healthy with us!

The space
Welcome to Fenway! Home of the Red Sox, we are within walking distances to shops, restaurants , night life and more! This apartment has two rooms and a fully equipped kitchen. Each room has a comfortable queen bed with clean linens. One of the bedrooms is shared with the living room. There are doors on both rooms for privacy. This unit is located on the third floor, two flights up! Common laundry is located in the basement! We look forward to hosting you!

Guest access
Keypad- Code will be released the day before check in.

Other things to note
